cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning (ML) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques to improve virtual keyboard search suggestion quality. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of NLP techniques to improve search suggestions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses privacy concerns and the use of decentralized training, which could place it in the categories of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper also discusses the evaluation of the model, which could place it in the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
